The course consist of lectures on basic principles and general problems in clinical pharmacology, and disease oriented small group seminars using problem-based approach or appraisal of published research articles.Objectives/eesmärkid:  After completion of the course the student is able to evaluate the need for pharmacotherapy and perform evidence based and safe pharmacotherapy.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completion of the course the student:
1. Is familiar with and able to use the basic terminology of clinical pharmacology and evidence based medicine; able to find, use and critically appraise drug information;
2. Is able to decide if pharmacotherapy is necessary, pose a measurable treatment goal, select a drug group and a drug based on efficacy, safety and cost, consider suitability of the chosen therapy to the patient, Is able to recognise an adverse drug reaction and to manage this, write a correct prescription, inform the patient and monitor the treatment.
